cs.CL, cs.DB, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.LG. 

The paper discusses natural language interfaces (NLI) for databases, which involves natural language processing (NLP) and artificial intelligence (AI) techniques. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category as it deals with NLP. cs.DB (Databases) is also highly likely as the paper specifically focuses on NLIs for databases. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.IR (Information Retrieval) are also possible sub-categories as they both involve AI techniques and information retrieval. Finally, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is a less likely sub-category, but still possible as machine learning is often used in NLP and AI applications.
